# Error Resolution Logging

## When to Log

Log to `ERROR_FIX_LOG.md` when resolving:

- **Build failures** — compilation errors, linker issues, CGO problems
- **Runtime errors** — panics, nil pointer dereferences, goroutine leaks
- **API errors** — Kalshi/Polymarket/OpenAI unexpected responses, schema changes, auth failures
- **Database errors** — SQLite migration failures, constraint violations, corruption
- **Deployment errors** — environment misconfiguration, missing dependencies
- **Any issue taking >5 minutes to diagnose**

## When NOT to Log

- Simple typos or syntax errors caught immediately
- Linter warnings resolved in <1 minute
- Expected test failures during TDD
- Known issues already documented in ERROR_FIX_LOG.md

## Category Prefixes

| Prefix | Area |
|---|---|
| `BUILD` | Go compilation, CGO, module resolution |
| `KALSHI` | Kalshi API adapter issues |
| `POLY` | Polymarket API adapter issues |
| `OPENAI` | OpenAI embedding API issues |
| `SQLITE` | Database schema, queries, migrations |
| `NORM` | Normalization layer (L2) issues |
| `EQUIV` | Equivalence detection (L3) issues |
| `ROUTE` | Routing engine (L4) issues |
| `CONFIG` | Viper/env configuration issues |
| `TEST` | Test infrastructure, fixtures, mocks |
| `CLI` | Cobra CLI command issues |

## Log Format

```markdown
### [CATEGORY-NNN] Short description
- **Date:** YYYY-MM-DD
- **Error:** Exact error message or observed behavior
- **Context:** What was being done when it occurred
- **Root Cause:** Why it happened
- **Fix:** What resolved it
- **Prevention:** How to avoid recurrence
```

## Numbering

Increment the number within each category (e.g., KALSHI-001, KALSHI-002). Check existing entries before assigning a number.
